### Aim:  
To determine if a given **linked list** contains a cycle.  

### Objectives:
- Detect cycles in a linked list by tracking visited nodes.  
- Use Floydâ€™s Cycle Detection Algorithm (fast and slow pointers) for an efficient solution.  
- Optimize space complexity to O(1) by avoiding additional data structures.

### Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool hasCycle(ListNode* head) {
        //22bet10067
        if (head == NULL || head->next == NULL) {
            return false;
        }
        ListNode* slow = head;
        ListNode* fast = head->next;
        while (fast != slow) {
            if (fast->next == NULL || fast->next->next == NULL) {
                return false;
            }
            slow = slow->next;
            fast = fast->next->next;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
